Christmas Night Luxor, 1912
darling Gopher 'The nicest things that hnppened to me today were receipt of your letter of Dec. 7, and the fact that Emily Morgan seent a little part of the day with us. Those two things kept me from wholly 'succumbinR to homesickness. I felt its touch on my shoulder, so to see all day long. The Serapis and Mr. Tuck and his party, of which Emily ~ Miss Nelson are two-ninths, came down from Aswan yesterday. They waves from the deck as they steamed by us, and soon after luncheon we went 0\ to the Serapis to call. Emily is certainly one of the sweetest things
all the world. I was as glad to see her 115 if she were my very own.
