Thursday, March 13, 1913 Speeding down the Nile
Bast beloved -at last we are on our homeward say. Of course it is going to take us two months and a half to get there, but four ; months have gone. te left Aswan early Friday morning and reached Lul'
too late Sunday A.M. for D. and me to go to church. We had expected;
to come do""n flying, heaving the current in our favo~, as well <M.S te;
tug, but mad winds and many sandbars interrupted our progress. Not
that D and I minded sit Was interesting to watch the crew getting n,
