heard's III
Yesterday, being Good Friday, I went to church. Doris d{ddt feel well so I went alone in the huge red motor car. The church Was ful and many, many men "dere there. That's one .. of the fire things about Englishmen -they stand steadfastly by the training of their youths in the matter of churchgoing. Coming out I stopped for a moment te look at the plain little tablet set in the hall at the end of the church in memory of that great hero Gordon. Outside the door I found l'li's. Romeyn and Emma \.'m sing for me.
